From Brian V Hughes Subject Re Quadra Anand Mani writes Besides the faster processor, the has SCSI , and as far as I know, faster I O due to separate processors handling those functions Mostly The Q does have a SCSI controller chip as it's SCSI chip, but it does not have the chips to use the Wide or Fast SCSI modes and therefore doesn't offer much more in the way of SCSI performance over the Q It does, howrever, have a faster I O controller than the Q this is where the real speed boost comes from Hades